\end{align}$

###Setting up a proportion

Corresponding sides of similar triangles are proportional, so we can set up and solve a proportion:

$\dfrac{MD}{PD}=\dfrac{\maroonD{MU}}{PA}$

We picked side $\maroonD{\overline{MU}}$ because we need to find its length.

We picked side $\overline{PA}$ because it corresponds to side $\maroonD{\overline{MU}}$.

Then we picked another pair of corresponding sides where we already knew the measurements.

$\begin{array}{rcl}
&\triangle UMD
\\
{\text{adjacent to } \atop \angle 1/\angle 2}
&\overbrace{\underbrace{\!\!\!\!\!\left\{ 
\dfrac{MD}{PD}=\dfrac{\maroonD{MU}}{PA}
\right\}\!\!\!\!\!}}
&{\text{opposite to } \atop \angle 1/\angle 2}
\\
&\triangle APD
\end{array}$

###Solving the proportion for $\maroonD{MU}$

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{MD}{PD}&=\dfrac{\maroonD{MU}}{PA}
\\\\
\dfrac{10}{3.75}&=\dfrac{\maroonD{MU}}{4.5}
\\\\
4.5\cdot\dfrac{10}{3.75}&=\dfrac{\maroonD{MU}}{\cancel{4.5}} \cdot \cancel{4.5}
\\\\
\maroonD{MU} &=12
\end{align}$
